`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Testing GPU shaders in Jest**: Since GLSL runs on the GPU and cannot be executed in Node.js, shader tests focus on two testable seams: (1) shader string structure verification (does the GLSL contain the right uniforms and constants?), and (2) the pure TypeScript uniform-building function (`buildGerstnerUniforms`) which maps the data model to shader inputs. This covers correctness of the data pipeline without needing a WebGL context.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

